title: 4 men found dead at bed and breakfast facility in Bundang - Yonhap News Agency
content:
SEONGNAM, South Korea, Aug. 26 (Yonhap) -- Four men were found dead Saturday at a bed and breakfast facility in Bundang, south of Seoul, sending police to investigate the cause of the deaths.

Police received a report from the operator of the lodging service around noon that "four men were left dead in the same room."

The four in their 30s and 40s reportedly arrived at the lodging establishment the previous evening. Police said no signs of foul play have been found in connection with the deaths so far, adding an investigation will be launched as to how they were related to each other and the exact circumstances of the deaths.



This photo, provided by the police, shows the Bundang Police Station in Seongnam. (PHOTO NOT FOR SALE) (Yonhap)

(END)

title: The Hoarders House That Became A Luxurious Bed & Breakfast - Looper
content:
The Hoarders House That Became A Luxurious Bed & Breakfast

It's not a typical reaction to any given episode of "Hoarders" to want to visit the homes featured on the show, nor would any of those homes seem like prime candidates for conversion into a bed and breakfast. But as unlikely as it might seem, one such home did indeed undergo that transformation, and it was notable enough to be reported in the New York Post.

The home in question is the Julian Price House, also known as Hillside, which was purchased by an interior decorator named Sandra Cowart back in 1975. At some point, Cowart succumbed to a latent tendency towards hoarding, eventually leading to the large Greensboro, North Carolina, estate being featured on Season 9, Episode 6 of "Hoarders" after the house was foreclosed on and its new owners attempted to clean it out and bring it back to some of its former majesty. While it isn't the most disturbing episode of "Hoarders" by any stretch, it is among the more memorable ones. However, the estate's reality TV fame eventually led to a third life as a successful bed and breakfast where you can book your own luxurious stay on the official Julian Price House site.

The episode shows Hillside's buyers in the tricky position of having to evict Cowart, who experienced a sad decline into hoarding over the course of her 40+ years of ownership of the property. But it has a somewhat happy ending, with Cowart working with the buyers to help clear the home and leaving on somewhat positive terms.

title: Borroe Fever! Why Shiba Inu and BNB Enthusiasts Are Making the Big Switch - Punch Newspapers
content:
Shiba Inu (SHIB) is making headlines for its struggles with high network patronage while Binance Coin (BNB) continues to grapple with its SEC lawsuit. At the same time, Borroe ($ROE), whose current trajectory is 25% up, has become one of the best defi projects on the market. Naturally, some investors are dumping Shiba Inu (SHIB) and Binance Coin (BNB) for Borroe ($ROE), but others question if it will really be a good crypto to buy now. Let’s see who might be right regarding Borroe ($ROE).

>>BUY $ROE TOKENS NOW<<

Shiba Inu’s (SHIB) Base Network, “Shibarium” Resumes Block Production After High Traffic Concerns

The Shibarium network that powers the Shiba Inu (SHIB) memecoin has struggled with unusual network activity increase in the past few days. Since Shiba Inu’s (SHIB) token burn on July 11, Shibarium’s network activity has been increasing.

Shiba Inu (SHIB) paused all block production on August 17 as Shibarium’s network activity reached unusually high activity levels. The network activity increase raised concerns about fund security, so Shibarium entered a failsafe mode aimed at protecting Shiba Inu’s (SHIB) user funds.

SHIB’s decline is partly due to the market-wide drop-off on August 17. Once the crypto market turns bullish, Shiba Inu (SHIB) could potentially rise by 14.4% to $0.000009505.

Binance Coin (BNB) Suffers in the Aftermath of Battle with the SEC

Binance Coin’s (BNB) crypto exchange has been locked in a legal tussle with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) since June 5, 2023.

The SEC had sued Binance for several regulatory breaches, including selling unregistered securities, misrepresenting trading controls, and operating unregistered exchanges. The battle led to the delisting of several crypto trading pairs in Binance’s US subsidiary.

Consequently, the legal tussles have led to a sharp drop in Binance Coin’s (BNB) value. Binance Coin’s (BNB) trading activity also declined in some regions as the SEC’s lawsuit raised credibility issues for Binance.

Then the crypto market crashed on August 17, causing Binance Coin (BNB) to fall further.

Yet, experts say Binance Coin (BNB) could rise by 38.5% to $300.51 if the regulatory issues around it clear up, leading to a rise in Binance Coin’s (BNB) trading activity.

The growth of the Internet has been very rapid since the early 2000s. It got boosted further with the creation of Web 3 technologies and cryptocurrencies. Many internet businesses need to work at lightning speed to ensure quality service delivery.

Borroe ($ROE) is a decentralized platform designed to improve the business efficiency of the Web 3.0 industry by providing secure, timely loans that are used to ensure the smooth running of business operations.

Borroe ($ROE) takes a new and radically different approach to revenue financing. It aims to cut out numerous bottlenecks like lengthy delays and limited access. Borroe ($ROE) ensures the wider availability of loans by creating a secure marketplace that attracts interested firms and individuals willing to invest in revenue financing.

Borroe’s ($ROE) users will enjoy priority notifications on new offers, discounts, and special recognition for individual contributions to the platform.
